    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n    <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n    <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n    <title>B+ Tree</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n        }\n        \n        .container {\n            width: 80%;\n            margin: 40px auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            border-radius: 10px;\n            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);\n        }\n        \n        .text {\n            font-size: 18px;\n            font-weight: bold;\n        }\n        \n        .button {\n            padding: 10px 20px;\n            background-color: #4CAF50;\n            color: #fff;\n            border: none;\n            border-radius: 5px;\n            cursor: pointer;\n        }\n        \n        .button:hover {\n            background-color: #3e8e41;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n        <h1>B+ Tree</h1>\n        <p>B+ Tree is a self-balancing search tree data structure that maintains the balance of the tree by rotating nodes.</p>\n        <p>A B+ Tree is a special type of B- Tree where each node has a maximum of two children, and each internal node has a minimum and maximum key.</p>\n        <p>The B+ Tree is composed of a root node, and each node has at most two children (left child and right child), and each internal node has a minimum and maximum key.</p>\n        <p>Key properties of a B+ Tree include:</p>\n        <ul>\n            <li>Each node has a maximum of two children.</li>\n            <li>Each internal node has a minimum and maximum key.</li>\n            <li>The tree is self-balancing, meaning that the height of the tree remains relatively constant even after insertions and deletions.</li>\n        </ul>\n        <p>How does it work?</p>\n        <p>A B+ Tree works by maintaining a balance between the height of the tree and the number of keys in the tree.</p>\n        <p>When a new key is inserted into the tree, the tree is rebalanced to ensure that the height remains relatively constant.</p>\n        <p>Rebalancing involves rotating nodes to maintain the balance of the tree.</p>\n        <p>Here's an example of how a B+ Tree is rebalanced:</p>\n        <img src=\"rebalance.png\" alt=\"Rebalance Example\">\n        <p>The goal of rebalancing is to ensure that the tree remains approximately balanced, which means that the height of the tree is around 2:1.</p>\n        <p>Here's an example of how a B+ Tree is structured:</p>\n        <img src=\"tree.png\" alt=\"B+ Tree Structure\">\n        <p>Each node in the tree has a key, a left child, and a right child.</p>\n        <p>The tree is structured in a way that allows for efficient search, insertion, and deletion of keys.</p>\n        <p>Here's an example of how a B+ Tree is used in a real-world application:</p>\n        <img src=\"example.png\" alt=\"B+ Tree in Use\">\n        <p>B+ Trees are widely used in many applications, including databases, file systems, and search engines.</p>\n        <p>They are particularly useful for large datasets where the number of keys is very high.</p>\n        <p>Here's an example of how a B+ Tree can be used to search for a specific key:</p>\n        <img src=\"search.png\" alt=\"B+ Tree Search\">\n        <button id=\"demo\">Click to Rebalance and Search</button>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        // Define the B+ Tree class\n        class BPlusTree {\n            constructor() {\n                this.root = null;\n                this.keys = [];\n            }\n\n            // Insert a key into the tree\n            insert(key) {\n                if (this.root === null) {\n                    this.root = new Node(key);\n                } else {\n                    this.root.insert(key);\n                }\n            }\n\n            // Rebalance the tree\n            rebalance() {\n                // Calculate the height of the tree\n                let height = this.getTreeHeight();\n\n                // Calculate the balance factor\n                let balanceFactor = this.getBalanceFactor(this.root);\n\n                // If the balance factor is greater than 1, the tree is unbalanced\n                if (balanceFactor > 1) {\n                    // If the tree is unbalanced to the right, rotate the right child\n                    if (balanceFactor > 0) {\n                        this.rightRotate(this.root);\n                    }\n\n                    // If the tree is unbalanced to the left, rotate the left child\n                    if (balanceFactor < 0) {\n                        this.leftRotate(this.root);\n                    }\n                }\n\n                // If the balance factor is less than -1, the tree is unbalanced\n                if (balanceFactor < -1) {\n                    // If the tree is unbalanced to the right, rotate the right child\n                    if (balanceFactor < 0) {\n                        this.rightRotate(this.root);\n                    }\n\n                    // If the tree is unbalanced to the left, rotate the left child\n                    if (balanceFactor > 0) {\n                        this.leftRotate(this.root);\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n\n            // Get the height of the tree\n            getTreeHeight() {\n                let height = 0;\n                let node = this.root;\n\n                while (node !== null) {\n                    height++;\n                    node = node.left;\n                }\n\n                return height;\n            }\n\n            // Get the balance factor of the tree\n            getBalanceFactor(node) {\n                let balanceFactor = 0;\n\n                while (node !== null) {\n                    balanceFactor++;\n\n                    if (node.left === null) {\n                        node = node.right;\n                    } else {\n                        node = node.left;\n                    }\n                }\n\n                return balanceFactor;\n            }\n\n            // Rotate the left child\n            leftRotate(node) {\n                let newRoot = node.left;\n                let newLeftChild = newRoot.right;\n                newRoot.right = newLeftChild;\n                newLeftChild.left = newRoot;\n\n                this.updateNode(node);\n                this.updateNode(newRoot);\n            }\n\n            // Rotate the right child\n            rightRotate(node) {\n                let newRoot = node.right;\n                let newRightChild = newRoot.left;\n                newRoot.left = newRightChild;\n                newRightChild.right = newRoot;\n\n                this.updateNode(node);\n                this.updateNode(newRoot);\n            }\n\n            // Update the node\n            updateNode(node) {\n                while (node !== null) {\n                    let child = node.left;\n                    while (child !== null) {\n                        let grandchild = child.right;\n                        while (grandchild !== null) {\n                            let parent = grandchild.left;\n                            while (parent !== null) {\n                                if (parent.key < child.key) {\n                                    let temp = parent;\n                                    parent = parent.right;\n                                    temp.right = child;\n                                    child.left = temp;\n                                    break;\n                                }\n                            }\n                            grandchild = grandchild.left;\n                        }\n                        child = child.right;\n                    }\n                    node = node.parent;\n                }\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Create a new B+ Tree\n        let tree = new BPlusTree();\n\n        // Insert keys into the tree\n        tree.insert(\"apple\");\n        tree.insert(\"banana\");\n        tree.insert(\"cherry\");\n\n        // Rebalance the tree\n        tree.rebalance();\n\n        // Search for a key in the tree\n        let key = \"banana\";\n        if (tree.keys.includes(key)) {\n            console.log(`Key ${key} found in the tree.`);\n        } else {\n            console.log(`Key ${key} not found in the tree.`);\n        }\n\n        // Rebalance the tree again\n        tree.rebalance();\n\n        // Search for a key in the tree again\n        key = \"cherry\";\n        if (tree.keys.includes(key)) {\n            console.log(`Key ${key} found in the tree.`);\n        } else {\n            console.log(`Key ${key} not found in the tree.`);\n        }\n    </script>\n\n    <script src=\"script.js\"></script>\n</body>\n</html>"
